<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,356,741]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254">
<bibRefCitation author="Thery" box="[199,347,500,525]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" refString="Thery, A. (1947) Buprestides d'Angola. Arquivos do Museo Bocage, 18, 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="1947">
Théry (
<number box="[280,338,500,524]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" value="1947.0">1947</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
listed among other 
<taxonomicName box="[568,669,500,524]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[568,669,500,524]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="254">Anthaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-species collected by the Monard´s expeditions also one specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Obenberger, 1922" authorityName="Obenberger" authorityYear="1922" box="[151,566,535,560]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosa">
<emphasis box="[151,354,536,560]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="254">Anthaxia luctuosa</emphasis>
Obenberger, 
<number box="[506,566,536,560]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" value="1922.0">1922</number>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[577,703,536,560]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosa">
<emphasis box="[577,703,536,560]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="254">A. luctuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kerremans, 1913 (Bily &amp; Kuban, 2010)" authorityName="Kerremans, 1913 (Bily &amp; Kuban" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albovillosa">
<emphasis box="[897,1053,536,560]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="254">A. albovillosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kerremans" box="[1060,1253,536,560]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" refString="Kerremans, C. (1913) Deuxieme supplement au Catalogue des Buprestides du Congo Belge. Revue de Zoologie Africaine, 2, 439 - 448." type="journal article" year="1913">
Kerremans, 
<number box="[1197,1253,536,560]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" value="1913.0">1913</number>
</bibRefCitation>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bily" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" refString="Bily, S. &amp; Kuban, V. (2010) A revision of the Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) melancholica and A. (H.) thunbergi species-groups (Coleoptera: Buprestidae: Buprestinae: Anthaxiini). Folia Heyrovskyana, series A, 18 (1 - 3), 25 - 58." type="journal article" year="2010">
Bílý &amp; Kubáň, 
<number box="[151,209,572,596]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and moreover also a homonym (
<taxonomicName authority="Lucas, 1846" authorityName="Lucas" authorityYear="1846" box="[586,856,572,597]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosa">
<emphasis box="[586,712,572,596]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="254">A. luctuosa</emphasis>
Lucas, 
<number box="[800,856,572,597]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" value="1846.0">1846</number>
</taxonomicName>
)—see 
<bibRefCitation author="Bily" box="[936,1058,572,597]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" refString="Bily, S. (2006) A revision of the Anthaxia (Anthaxia) funerula species-group (Coleoptera: Buprestidae: Anthaxiini). Folia Heyrovskyana, Supplementum 12, 1 - 75." type="journal article" year="2006">
Bílý, 
<number box="[998,1058,572,597]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,356,741]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254">
After having studied the specimen determined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Thery" box="[793,947,607,632]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" refString="Thery, A. (1947) Buprestides d'Angola. Arquivos do Museo Bocage, 18, 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="1947">
Théry (
<number box="[880,939,608,632]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" value="1947.0">1947</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName box="[994,1125,608,632]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosa">
<emphasis box="[994,1125,608,632]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="254">A. luctuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and compared it with the 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,644,669]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254">holotype</typeStatus>
of the recently described 
<taxonomicName box="[565,759,644,668]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puchneri" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[565,590,644,667]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="254">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[611,638,645,668]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="254">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[659,759,644,668]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="254">puchneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[779,866,644,669]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1784,1807]" captionTargetBox="[232,1358,848,1679]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,796,1764]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 20. Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) puchneri Bílý &amp; Sakalian, 2014. 18 — specimen determined by Théry (1947) as A. (H.) luctuosa Obenberger, 1922, 8.0 mm; 19 — the same, original labelling; 20 — A. (H.) puchneri Bílý &amp; Sakalian, 1914, holotype, 8.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244477/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="254">
Fig. 
<number box="[837,866,644,668]" pageId="8" pageNumber="254" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
) I found them to be conspecific. The female is unknown.
</paragraph>
